Bangladesh Olympic chief Fired
DHAKA , December 24 ( Xinhua ) -- The government Thursday fired the chief of the Bangladesh Olympic Association retired lieutenant general M. Mahbubur Rahman , according to a report .
Rahman , a former army chief , had been heading the national Olympic Association since 1995 .
And the official BSS news agency , quoting an official notice , said Rahman has been " relieved " of the post and the order " will be effective forthwith . "
It gave no reason , but added the executive committee of the Olympic Association had also been dissolved with immediate effect " in a bid to form a new committee . "
